The <b>Lovely Cotinga</b> (<i>Cotinga amabilis</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cotingidae" title="Cotingidae" class="mw-redirect">Cotingidae</a> family. It is found in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_America" title="Central America">Central America</a> from southern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a> through <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala" title="Guatemala">Guatemala</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belize" title="Belize">Belize</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honduras" title="Honduras">Honduras</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicaragua" title="Nicaragua">Nicaragua</a> to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costa_Rica" title="Costa Rica">Costa Rica</a> with reports from western <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panama" title="Panama">Panama</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-IUCN2012_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-IUCN2012-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are tropical moist lowland <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a> and heavily degraded former forest.<sup id="cite_ref-IUCN2012_1-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-IUCN2012-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>
